  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Braille Bricks: a tool for Blind Children literacy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Dorina Foundation, in partnership with the Lego Foundation, brings to the world a toy which will help blind children towards literacy all over the globe: The Braille Bricks! Each block represents a letter in the braille alphabet. The goal is to encourage blind children to play with others and learn. But, we need your help!  To be delivered for free to thousands of Brazilian schools, we need funds for logistics. We&apos;ll also give trainning to the teachers, so they can fully use the Bricks.</narrative>
  </description>
